/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
Cargo.lock

# Exception: the fuzz subcrate is a binary-shaped project (cargo-fuzz
# targets compile to executables), so its Cargo.lock IS committed to
# keep reproducible fuzz builds across runs. Same pattern as the
# `oxideav-id3` / `oxideav-mkv` fuzz subcrates.
!fuzz/Cargo.lock
